  "prompt": "Which are some of the characteristics of pragmatism?",
  "response": "Here are some key characteristics of pragmatism:\n\n1. Practical consequences\n- Emphasizes the practical outcomes and real-world implications of ideas\n- Focuses on what works rather than abstract theoretical principles\n\n2. Problem-solving orientation\n- Prioritizes finding effective solutions to concrete problems\n- Values experimentation and testing ideas through practical application\n\n3. Flexibility and adaptability\n- Views knowledge as provisional and subject to revision\n- Encourages open-mindedness and willingness to change beliefs based on new evidence\n\n4. Emphasis on experience\n- Views experience as the primary source of knowledge\n- Believes that understanding emerges through active engagement with the world\n\n5. Anti-foundationalism\n- Rejects absolute or universal truths\n- Considers knowledge as contextual and dependent on specific circumstances\n\n6. Instrumentalism\n- Sees ideas and theories as tools for understanding and solving problems\n- Judges concepts by their utility and effectiveness\n\n7. Empirical approach\n- Values scientific method and observable evidence\n- Promotes systematic investigation and verification of ideas\n\n8. Pluralistic perspective\n- Recognizes multiple valid interpretations and approaches\n- Encourages dialogue and consideration of diverse viewpoints\n\nThese characteristics reflect pragmatism's core philosophical commitment to practical reasoning and meaningful action.",
